place_description: Seattle-based coffeehouse chain known for its signature roasts, light bites and WiFi availability.

reviews_data.review_text: Super friendly barista. Just wish there was more than one staffed as there was a long line and I felt bad that he was alone.
One of the better Starbucks within an 8 mile radius. They are super busy but the line moves quickly. However,  they have staff changes often.

I consistently have the best experience at starbucks in the morning everytime I go!! The barista, juno, never fails to make the best drinks I can tell she puts a lot of love, care, and precision into everything she makes! She deserves a raise!
Usually very crowded. Service is excellent as far as friendliness but they seem to always forget the extra caramel in my teens order.
Wished I had not but i did see a cockroach crawling on a container that held the plastic coffee cup lids.

The cafe was pretty packed today, given it is a Sunday, but service was quick! I ordered a grande light ice matcha, with 5 pumps of vanilla and oat milk, extra shaken. All I can say is WOW. I drink a lot of matcha and today, this was the best matcha I've ever had. I give all the credit to Tim, the barista who really put the time and love into my matcha. This is such a huge deal for me because 9/10 times I order matcha, it's usually a chalky consistency. But it was so creamy and well built, that I will only have Tim make my drink from now on! As a barista myself, I know when you have a great experience like this, it always makes you come back for more. So if you're reading this Tim, THANK YOU!

EDIT - 12/18/23
Scout is such a beast and love his energy. I was in a hurry and needed some pumps of vanilla and was willing to pay (because I only like Starbucks vanilla syrup) and he remembered me and helped me out! Thanks so much, you're awesome!!

Starbucks is always great... But it usually comes with happy employees that are knowledgable... 
Not this time, it seemed as if no one knew what was going on,  and when I asked air a particular price, no one could come up with an answer until 2 employees reached out to whom I thought was a manager and she simply did a price check to let me know. This took 12 minutes. I'm never the one to complain to this extent and I'm sorry but It's Starbucks representation... and what if this was my first visit to any location!?

Worst service EVER. Never even got my drinks. They never apologized for the fact that it didn't print order but they could see it on their computer. I couldn't wait any longer, asked for a refund and the guy complained to me about have to refund me the entire time he was doing it. Rude, Rude, Rude. The rest of the workers were just laughing and socializing the entire time I was in there.

Very disappointed and frustrated with this location. I ordered on the mobile app a breakfast sandwich with no egg or cheese due to a dietary restriction. I grabbed it on the way to work and when I got there it had egg and cheese, which meant I couldn't eat it. I totally understand mistakes happen, but it's happened a couple times at this location and it is a pretty big let down to have to skip breakfast even though you paid for one and drove to get it. Customizations should be taken seriously, if I hadn't noticed and bit into it I could've gotten sick, had to miss work, etc. I decided to try to at least get my money back and was unable to get my call answered. I called again and again and several times the phone was picked up and I was immediately hung up on. I didn't feel like I should have to drive out of my way to go into a Starbucks and physically ask for a refund when it was their mistake. After tying to call for hours and getting hung up on, I eventually decided to call the general Starbucks number and had to use half my lunch break on the phone to get a refund. This Starbucks needs to seriously pay attention to modifications and not hang up on customers. It was all such an ordeal when it didn't need to me. I will not be going to this Starbucks again.

I came this morning to grab a coffee with my mom in the morning 8:30 am . To this place is a coffee shop where you want to see a friendly and awake person. A guy with a very rude sleepy attitude took my order I was like okay you know people can have a bad day sometimes I get it but then I came to ask for sugar he didn't even ask what kind he just hand me like 4 Splenda sugars I was like Can you please give me the cane sugar and he look at me like I was a horrible person and give him and a hard day . he hand me the sugar like he didn't even wanted to and drop one  he didn't care at all I pick up and I was wow thank you and he went back and didn't even care . Sorry but I usually come to Starbucks for a good coffee and to sit down and enjoy it but with this person being rude since the beginning I don't know !
